cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or benchmark in research, please cite it as below."
title: "GovernedAgentBench and the HAI reference runtime (Told or Enforced)"
abstract: >-
  GovernedAgentBench separates the two levers a harness can use to keep an
  agent within a rule: specifying the rule in the in-context contract, and
  enforcing it in the runtime. It crosses told-versus-withheld with
  enforced-versus-off per governance mechanism, scored by a deterministic
  offline scorer, against HAI, a frozen non-clinical personal-wellness
  reference runtime. Companion artifact to the preprint "Told or Enforced:
  When In-Context Contracts Substitute for Runtime Enforcement in Agent
  Harnesses."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Dom
    family-names: Colligan
repository-code: "https://github.com/dtcolligan/health_agent_infra"
url: "https://github.com/dtcolligan/health_agent_infra"
license: MIT
keywords:
